{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"alias":"curly-mild-chupacabra","description":"Harden the T5c security-overlay rubric prompt against out-of-scope and duplicate advisory findings, without changing its posture (advisory @ 0.95) or its recall on genuinely in-scope security gaps.\n\nEvidence: T5c produced 288 advisory findings in the last 7 days with zero blocks ever; observed failure shapes include (a) findings about credentials/assets the plan does not touch (e.g. demanding rotation of a Gerrit HTTP password on a plan that only destroys an SSM copy), and (b) same-round near-duplicates (ticket 9e76: two findings both demanding temp-key-file deletion). ADR 0018's trust-boundary scope gate already bounds WHEN T5c fires; this task bounds WHAT it may claim once fired.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] src/rebar/llm/reviewers/plan_review_T5c.md gains an explicit in-plan-asset scope rule: a finding must name the plan section/step that creates, modifies, or transmits the asset at issue; assets merely adjacent to the plan (existing credentials, services, or stores the plan does not touch) are out of scope and must not be findings. Oracle: `grep -ni \"does not touch\\|in-plan\" src/rebar/llm/reviewers/plan_review_T5c.md` returns at least one hit.\n- [ ] The prompt gains a same-round dedup rule: one finding per (surface, defect) pair; additional criteria angles on the same pair are folded into that finding's text, not emitted separately. Oracle: `grep -ni \"one finding per\" src/rebar/llm/reviewers/plan_review_T5c.md` returns a hit.\n- [ ] The derived prompt index is regenerated if the build requires it and the CI prompt-drift gate passes. Oracle: `make lint && make test` green locally; the prompt-index drift check (part of the test suite) passes.\n- [ ] No routing change: src/rebar/llm/plan_review/criteria_routing.json is byte-identical for the T5c entry. Oracle: `git diff --stat -- src/rebar/llm/plan_review/criteria_routing.json` is empty.\n\nFiles: src/rebar/llm/reviewers/plan_review_T5c.md (+ regenerated prompt index if applicable).","id":"d156-7eb5-b4f0-40c3","parent_id":"d195-aeb8-2400-484b","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"T5c security-overlay prompt hygiene: in-plan-asset scope + same-round dedup"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784085071274161001,"uuid":"5f8a9e55-9e96-466b-87c5-8301afadb88f"}